            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Genesis.11:1-13:4",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EGenesis%2011%3A1-13%3A4%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_1%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EGenesis%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Tower%20of%20Babel%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20one%20time%20all%20the%20people%20of%20the%20world%20spoke%20the%20same%20language%20and%20used%20the%20same%20words.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_2%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20the%20people%20migrated%20to%20the%20east%2C%20they%20found%20a%20plain%20in%20the%20land%20of%20Babylonia%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EShinar.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20settled%20there.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_3%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20began%20saying%20to%20each%20other%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLet%26%23x2019%3Bs%20make%20bricks%20and%20harden%20them%20with%20fire.%26%23x201D%3B%20(In%20this%20region%20bricks%20were%20used%20instead%20of%20stone%2C%20and%20tar%20was%20used%20for%20mortar.)%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_4%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20they%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BCome%2C%20let%26%23x2019%3Bs%20build%20a%20great%20city%20for%20ourselves%20with%20a%20tower%20that%20reaches%20into%20the%20sky.%20This%20will%20make%20us%20famous%20and%20keep%20us%20from%20being%20scattered%20all%20over%20the%20world.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_5%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20came%20down%20to%20look%20at%20the%20city%20and%20the%20tower%20the%20people%20were%20building.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_6%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BLook!%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20said.%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20people%20are%20united%2C%20and%20they%20all%20speak%20the%20same%20language.%20After%20this%2C%20nothing%20they%20set%20out%20to%20do%20will%20be%20impossible%20for%20them!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_7%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3ECome%2C%20let%26%23x2019%3Bs%20go%20down%20and%20confuse%20the%20people%20with%20different%20languages.%20Then%20they%20won%26%23x2019%3Bt%20be%20able%20to%20understand%20each%20other.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_8%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20that%20way%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20scattered%20them%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20and%20they%20stopped%20building%20the%20city.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_9%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThat%20is%20why%20the%20city%20was%20called%20Babel%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EBabylon.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EBabel%3C%2Fem%3E%20sounds%20like%20a%20Hebrew%20term%20that%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Bconfusion.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%20because%20that%20is%20where%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20confused%20the%20people%20with%20different%20languages.%20In%20this%20way%20he%20scattered%20them%20all%20over%20the%20world.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_10%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Line%20of%20Descent%20from%20Shem%20to%20Abram%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20is%20the%20account%20of%20Shem%26%23x2019%3Bs%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging-sp%22%3ETwo%20years%20after%20the%20great%20flood%2C%20when%20Shem%20was%20100%26%23xA0%3Byears%20old%2C%20he%20became%20the%20father%20of%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A10%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20ancestor%20of%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2011%3A12%2C%2014%2C%2016%2C%2018%2C%2020%2C%2022%2C%2024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Arphaxad.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_11%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20the%20birth%20of%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A11%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20birth%20of%20this%20ancestor%20of%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20in%2011%3A13%2C%2015%2C%2017%2C%2019%2C%2021%2C%2023%2C%2025.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Arphaxad%2C%20Shem%20lived%20another%20500%26%23xA0%3Byears%20and%20had%20other%20sons%20and%20daughters.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_11_12%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Arphaxad%20was%2035%26%23xA0%3Byears%20old%2C%20he%